{"parse":{"title":"Roman Charity","pageid":4547535,"revid":855558764,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mei,_Bernardino_-_Caritas_romana_-_17th_century.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Mei%2C_Bernardino_-_Caritas_romana_-_17th_century.jpg/220px-Mei%2C_Bernardino_-_Caritas_romana_-_17th_century.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"164\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/37/Mei%2C_Bernardino_-_Caritas_romana_-_17th_century.jpg/330px-Mei%2C_Bernardino_-_Caritas_romana_-_17th_century.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Mei%2C_Bernardino_-_Caritas_romana_-_17th_century.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"397\" data-file-height=\"296\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mei,_Bernardino_-_Caritas_romana_-_17th_century.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>Roman Charity</i>, by <a href=\"/wiki/Bernardino_Mei\" title=\"Bernardino Mei\">Bernardino Mei</a></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Roman Charity</b> (Latin <i><b>Caritas romana</b></i>; Italian <i><b>Carit\u00e0 Romana</b></i>) is the <a href=\"/wiki/Exemplum\" title=\"Exemplum\">exemplary story</a> of a woman, Pero, who secretly <a href=\"/wiki/Breastfeeding\" title=\"Breastfeeding\">breastfeeds</a> her father, Cimon, after he is incarcerated and sentenced to death by starvation. <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Artists&#39;_depictions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Artists' depictions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Notes_and_references\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes and references</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Roman_Charity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The story is recorded in <i><a href=\"/wiki/Factorum_ac_dictorum_memorabilium\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Factorum ac dictorum memorabilium\">Factorum ac dictorum memorabilium</a></i> (Nine Books of Memorable Acts and Sayings of the Ancient Romans)<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> by the ancient Roman historian <a href=\"/wiki/Valerius_Maximus\" title=\"Valerius Maximus\">Valerius Maximus</a>, and was presented as a great act of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Pietas\" title=\"Pietas\">pietas</a></i> (i.e., filial piety) and Roman honour. A painting in the <a href=\"/wiki/Pietas_(goddess)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pietas (goddess)\">Temple of Pietas</a> depicted the scene.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Among Romans, the theme had mythological echoes in <a href=\"/wiki/Juno_(mythology)\" title=\"Juno (mythology)\">Juno</a>'s breastfeeding of the adult <a href=\"/wiki/Hercules\" title=\"Hercules\">Hercules</a>, an <a href=\"/wiki/Etruscan_mythology\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Etruscan mythology\">Etruscan myth</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tleft\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ghent_relief.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7d/Ghent_relief.jpg/220px-Ghent_relief.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7d/Ghent_relief.jpg/330px-Ghent_relief.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7d/Ghent_relief.jpg/440px-Ghent_relief.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"768\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Ghent_relief.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>Mammelokker</i>, <a href=\"/wiki/Belfry_of_Ghent\" title=\"Belfry of Ghent\">Belfry of Ghent</a></div></div></div>\n<p>The story of Cimon is predated, however, by an almost identical story recorded by Roman historian Valerius Maximus, later retold by Pliny the Elder (23-79), of a jailed plebeian woman who was nursed by her daughter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Yalom_(2013)_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Yalom_(2013)-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Historians note that Renaissance and Baroque depictions have more incestuous overtones.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Yalom_(2013)_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Yalom_(2013)-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries, many European artists depicted the scene.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Paul_Rubens\" title=\"Peter Paul Rubens\">Peter Paul Rubens</a> is known to have painted several versions. <a href=\"/wiki/Baroque_painting\" title=\"Baroque painting\">Baroque</a> artist <a href=\"/wiki/Caravaggio\" title=\"Caravaggio\">Caravaggio</a> also featured the scene in his work from 1606, <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Seven_Works_of_Mercy_(Caravaggio)\" title=\"The Seven Works of Mercy (Caravaggio)\">The Seven Works of Mercy</a></i>. <a href=\"/wiki/Neoclassicism\" title=\"Neoclassicism\">Neoclassical</a> depictions tended to be more subdued.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> The original legend does not mention Pero's child. This element was introduced in the 17th century in order to prevent an interpretation that there was something incestuous about the deed. At the same time the inclusion of the infant added a new level of meaning to the story as the three figures would represent the three generations and could therefore also be interpreted as an allegory of the three ages of man.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> A small annex to the <a href=\"/wiki/Belfry_of_Ghent\" title=\"Belfry of Ghent\">Belfry of Ghent</a> dating from 1741, included a sculpture of Roman Charity poised high above the front doorway.  It is referred to as 'mammelokker', which translates from Dutch as 'breast sucker'.<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the 20th century a fictional account of Roman Charity was presented in <a href=\"/wiki/John_Steinbeck\" title=\"John Steinbeck\">John Steinbeck</a>'s <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Grapes_of_Wrath\" title=\"The Grapes of Wrath\">The Grapes of Wrath</a></i> (1939).<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> At the end of the novel, Rosasharn (Rose of Sharon) nurses a sick and starving man in the corner of a barn. The 1969 painting <i><a href=\"/wiki/Partisan_Ballad\" title=\"Partisan Ballad\">Partisan Ballad</a></i> by <a href=\"/wiki/Mai_Dantsig\" title=\"Mai Dantsig\">Mai Dantsig</a> also echoes Roman Charity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The 1973 surrealist film <i><a href=\"/wiki/O_Lucky_Man!\" title=\"O Lucky Man!\">O Lucky Man!</a></i> also contains a scene of Roman Charity when the protagonist is starving and a vicar's wife nurses him rather than let him plunder the food gathered for an offering.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Artists.27_depictions\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Artists'_depictions\">Artists' depictions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Roman_Charity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Artists&#039; depictions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Affresco_romano_-_Pompei_-_Micon_e_Pero.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Affresco_romano_-_Pompei_-_Micon_e_Pero.jpg/90px-Affresco_romano_-_Pompei_-_Micon_e_Pero.jpg\" width=\"90\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Affresco_romano_-_Pompei_-_Micon_e_Pero.jpg/135px-Affresco_romano_-_Pompei_-_Micon_e_Pero.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Affresco_romano_-_Pompei_-_Micon_e_Pero.jpg/180px-Affresco_romano_-_Pompei_-_Micon_e_Pero.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2304\" data-file-height=\"3072\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<center>Fresco from <a href=\"/wiki/Pompeii\" title=\"Pompeii\">Pompeii</a><br />Artist unknown. <br />Mid 1st century CE<center>\n\t\t\t</center></center></div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Roman_Charity_c.1500-1520.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Roman_Charity_c.1500-1520.jpg/120px-Roman_Charity_c.1500-1520.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Roman_Charity_c.1500-1520.jpg/180px-Roman_Charity_c.1500-1520.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0e/Roman_Charity_c.1500-1520.jpg/240px-Roman_Charity_c.1500-1520.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"408\" data-file-height=\"408\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<center>Artist unknown.<br />(c. 1500-1520)<center>\n\t\t\t</center></center></div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Cimon_and_Pero_-_Hans_Sebald_Beham.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Cimon_and_Pero_-_Hans_Sebald_Beham.jpg/82px-Cimon_and_Pero_-_Hans_Sebald_Beham.jpg\" width=\"82\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Cimon_and_Pero_-_Hans_Sebald_Beham.jpg/123px-Cimon_and_Pero_-_Hans_Sebald_Beham.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Cimon_and_Pero_-_Hans_Sebald_Beham.jpg/164px-Cimon_and_Pero_-_Hans_Sebald_Beham.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"821\" data-file-height=\"1200\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<center><a href=\"/wiki/Hans_Sebald_Beham\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hans Sebald Beham\">Hans Sebald Beham</a><br />(1544)<center>\n\t\t\t</center></center></div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:28.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Roman_Charity_-_Pieter_Pauwel_Reubens.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Roman_Charity_-_Pieter_Pauwel_Reubens.jpg/120px-Roman_Charity_-_Pieter_Pauwel_Reubens.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"93\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Roman_Charity_-_Pieter_Pauwel_Reubens.jpg/180px-Roman_Charity_-_Pieter_Pauwel_Reubens.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c8/Roman_Charity_-_Pieter_Pauwel_Reubens.jpg/240px-Roman_Charity_-_Pieter_Pauwel_Reubens.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3302\" data-file-height=\"2564\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<center><a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Paul_Rubens\" title=\"Peter Paul Rubens\">Peter Paul Rubens</a><br />(c. 1612)<center>\n\t\t\t</center></center></div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:27.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Jan_Janssens_-_Roman_Caritas.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/Jan_Janssens_-_Roman_Caritas.jpg/120px-Jan_Janssens_-_Roman_Caritas.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"95\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/Jan_Janssens_-_Roman_Caritas.jpg/180px-Jan_Janssens_-_Roman_Caritas.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/Jan_Janssens_-_Roman_Caritas.jpg/240px-Jan_Janssens_-_Roman_Caritas.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"958\" data-file-height=\"759\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<center><a href=\"/wiki/Jan_Janssens\" title=\"Jan Janssens\">Jan Janssens</a><br />(1620-25)<center>\n\t\t\t</center></center></div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:25px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Roman_Charity,_Cimon_and_Peres_-_Dirck_Van_Baburen.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Roman_Charity%2C_Cimon_and_Peres_-_Dirck_Van_Baburen.jpg/120px-Roman_Charity%2C_Cimon_and_Peres_-_Dirck_Van_Baburen.jpg\" width=\"120\" height=\"100\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Roman_Charity%2C_Cimon_and_Peres_-_Dirck_Van_Baburen.jpg/180px-Roman_Charity%2C_Cimon_and_Peres_-_Dirck_Van_Baburen.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Roman_Charity%2C_Cimon_and_Peres_-_Dirck_Van_Baburen.jpg/240px-Roman_Charity%2C_Cimon_and_Peres_-_Dirck_Van_Baburen.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"522\" data-file-height=\"433\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<center><a href=\"/wiki/Dirck_Van_Baburen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dirck Van Baburen\">Dirck Van Baburen</a><br />(c. 1623)<center>\n\t\t\t</center></center></div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 150px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Gaspar_de_Crayer_-_Caritas_Romana_(Prado).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Gaspar_de_Crayer_-_Caritas_Romana_%28Prado%29.jpg/86px-Gaspar_de_Crayer_-_Caritas_Romana_%28Prado%29.jpg\" width=\"86\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Gaspar_de_Crayer_-_Caritas_Romana_%28Prado%29.jpg/129px-Gaspar_de_Crayer_-_Caritas_Romana_%28Prado%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1e/Gaspar_de_Crayer_-_Caritas_Romana_%28Prado%29.jpg/172px-Gaspar_de_Crayer_-_Caritas_Romana_%28Prado%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2121\" data-file-height=\"2952\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<center><a href=\"/wiki/Gaspar_de_Crayer\" title=\"Gaspar de Crayer\">Gaspar de Crayer</a><br />(c. 1625)<center>\n\t\t\t</center></center></div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 155px\"><div style=\"width: 155px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=